org.nodex.java.core

Interface Immutable


  • public interface Immutable

    This is a marker interface which, if implement by a class, allows instances of that class to be stored in SharedData structures.

    Use this with caution, only mark classes with Immutable if you really know they are safe to be used concurrently by multiple threads. The shared data structures only take certain types for a reason - to stop you having to worry about concurrency.

    Author:
    Tim Fox
